    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's just what people say to be nice. it doesn't feel true. i look at my contact list and my slack notifications and it's all just... transactional. if i didn't log in tomorrow, or next week, or next month... there wouldn't be a gap. there'd just be a little less noise in the system. it feels like it would just be a quiet, seamless transition. maybe that's just how things are supposed to be.",
